This is almost certainly a dupe of either 73881 (which is fixed as of last
night), or 72205 (which I am working on right now.)

If it's the former, it happens when you delete the last test case in a suite. 
You can avoid the problem by creating another test suite before you save.  Or,
if you have already saved the test and gotten tehn exception, you can still then
add another test case it will correct the problem and allow you to save the model.

If it's the latter, then you have deleted a test case but still have an
invocation of that test case in your test suite's behavior.   This should be
automatically removed for you, but until I have fixed it (still trying for 3.2
i2), you can correct the problem by removing the invocation of the non-existant
test case.


*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 73881 ***
